        Constructor
        Parameters:
        problem - the problem to solve.
        maxEvaluations - the max number of evaluation to realize.
        populationSize - the population size (the number of solutions at the beginning of each generation).
        matingPoolSize - the mating pool size (the number of solutions resulting of selection process).
        offspringPopulationSize - the offspring population size (the number of solutions resulting of crossover and mutation process).
        crossoverOperator - the crossover operator.
        mutationOperator - the mutation operator.
        selectionOperator - the selection operator.
        dominanceComparator - the dominance operator.
        evaluator - the solution evaluator.

      • reproduction

        protected List<S> reproduction(List<S> matingPool)
        This methods iteratively applies a CrossoverOperator a MutationOperator to the population to create the offspring population. The population size must be divisible by the number of parents required by the CrossoverOperator; this way, the needed parents are taken sequentially from the population.

        The number of solutions returned by the CrossoverOperator must be equal to the offspringPopulationSize state variable

        Specified by:
        reproduction in class AbstractEvolutionaryAlgorithm<S extends Solution<?>>
        Parameters:
        matingPool - the mating Pool
        Returns:
        The new created offspring population
